guments of influential texts in each field, a supplementary reading list and a list of works cited  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aCriticism. 0aLiteraturexHistory and criticismxTheory, etc. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBarker, Jill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarthes, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaudrillard, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhabha, Homi K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrannigan, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButler, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastle, Terry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChambers, lain, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChow, Rey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCurrie, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDerrida, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDollimore, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEagleton, Terry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGallagher, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldman, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaslett, Moyra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeath, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJameson, Fredric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJauss, Hans-Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocab